itemDescription: English World War I flying ace

wikipedia_page.main: Captain Thomas Walter Nash  (25 November 1891 – 23 October 1918) was a British World War I flying ace credited with eight aerial victories.

response: Thomas Nash was a relative of Shakespeare.
